This paper discusses the Book Citation Index, which is a database for indexing books and book chapters. The paper focuses on analyzing impact indicators for scientific publishers in the Social Sciences and Humanities fields. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as the paper discusses a new database for indexing books. The paper also discusses bibliometric analysis, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and library science (cs.LIS). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI) as it discusses rankings and indicators for scientific publishers.
